WebkitBoxAlign.description:
The **`box-align`** CSS property specifies how an element aligns its contents across its layout in a perpendicular direction. The effect of the property is only visible if there is extra space in the box.

**Syntax**: `start | center | end | baseline | stretch`

**Initial value**: `stretch`
WebkitBoxAlign.title: WebkitBoxAlign

WebkitBoxDirection.description:
The **`box-direction`** CSS property specifies whether a box lays out its contents normally (from the top or left edge), or in reverse (from the bottom or right edge).

**Syntax**: `normal | reverse | inherit`

**Initial value**: `normal`
WebkitBoxDirection.title: WebkitBoxDirection

WebkitBoxFlex.description:
The **`-moz-box-flex`** and **`-webkit-box-flex`** CSS properties specify how a `-moz-box` or `-webkit-box` grows to fill the box that contains it, in the direction of the containing box's layout.

**Syntax**: `<number>`

**Initial value**: `0`
WebkitBoxFlex.title: WebkitBoxFlex

WebkitBoxFlexGroup.description:
The **`box-flex-group`** CSS property assigns the flexbox's child elements to a flex group.

**Syntax**: `<integer>`

**Initial value**: `1`
WebkitBoxFlexGroup.title: WebkitBoxFlexGroup

WebkitBoxLines.description:
The **`box-lines`** CSS property determines whether the box may have a single or multiple lines (rows for horizontally oriented boxes, columns for vertically oriented boxes).

**Syntax**: `single | multiple`

**Initial value**: `single`
WebkitBoxLines.title: WebkitBoxLines

WebkitBoxOrdinalGroup.description:

**Syntax**: `<integer>`

**Initial value**: `1`
WebkitBoxOrdinalGroup.title: WebkitBoxOrdinalGroup

WebkitBoxOrient.description:
The **`box-orient`** CSS property sets whether an element lays out its contents horizontally or vertically.

**Syntax**: `horizontal | vertical | inline-axis | block-axis | inherit`

**Initial value**: `inline-axis`
WebkitBoxOrient.title: WebkitBoxOrient

WebkitBoxPack.description:
The **`-moz-box-pack`** and **`-webkit-box-pack`** CSS properties specify how a `-moz-box` or `-webkit-box` packs its contents in the direction of its layout. The effect of this is only visible if there is extra space in the box.

**Syntax**: `start | center | end | justify`

**Initial value**: `start`
WebkitBoxPack.title: WebkitBoxPack

inputMode.description: Hints at the type of data that might be entered by the user while editing the element or its contents
inputMode.title: inputMode

is.description: Specify that a standard HTML element should behave like a defined custom built-in element
is.title: is

aria-activedescendant.description: Identifies the currently active element when DOM focus is on a composite widget, textbox, group, or application.
aria-activedescendant.title: aria-activedescendant

aria-atomic.description: Indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the aria-relevant attribute.
aria-atomic.title: aria-atomic

aria-autocomplete.description:
Indicates whether inputting text could trigger display of one or more predictions of the user's intended value for an input and specifies how predictions would be
presented if they are made.
aria-autocomplete.title: aria-autocomplete

aria-braillelabel.description: Defines a string value that labels the current element, which is intended to be converted into Braille.
aria-braillelabel.title: aria-braillelabel

aria-brailleroledescription.description: Defines a human-readable, author-localized abbreviated description for the role of an element, which is intended to be converted into Braille.
aria-brailleroledescription.title: aria-brailleroledescription

aria-checked.description: Indicates the current "checked" state of checkboxes, radio buttons, and other widgets.
aria-checked.title: aria-checked

aria-colcount.description: Defines the total number of columns in a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-colcount.title: aria-colcount

aria-colindex.description: Defines an element's column index or position with respect to the total number of columns within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-colindex.title: aria-colindex

aria-colindextext.description: Defines a human readable text alternative of aria-colindex.
aria-colindextext.title: aria-colindextext

aria-colspan.description: Defines the number of columns spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-colspan.title: aria-colspan

aria-controls.description: Identifies the element (or elements) whose contents or presence are controlled by the current element.
aria-controls.title: aria-controls

aria-current.description: Indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.
aria-current.title: aria-current

aria-describedby.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that describes the object.
aria-describedby.title: aria-describedby

aria-description.description: Defines a string value that describes or annotates the current element.
aria-description.title: aria-description

aria-details.description: Identifies the element that provides a detailed, extended description for the object.
aria-details.title: aria-details

aria-disabled.description: Indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable.
aria-disabled.title: aria-disabled

aria-dropeffect.description: Indicates what functions can be performed when a dragged object is released on the drop target.
aria-dropeffect.title: aria-dropeffect

aria-errormessage.description: Identifies the element that provides an error message for the object.
aria-errormessage.title: aria-errormessage

aria-expanded.description: Indicates whether the element, or another grouping element it controls, is currently expanded or collapsed.
aria-expanded.title: aria-expanded

aria-flowto.description:
Identifies the next element (or elements) in an alternate reading order of content which, at the user's discretion,
allows assistive technology to override the general default of reading in document source order.
aria-flowto.title: aria-flowto

aria-grabbed.description: Indicates an element's "grabbed" state in a drag-and-drop operation.
aria-grabbed.title: aria-grabbed

aria-haspopup.description: Indicates the availability and type of interactive popup element, such as menu or dialog, that can be triggered by an element.
aria-haspopup.title: aria-haspopup

aria-hidden.description: Indicates whether the element is exposed to an accessibility API.
aria-hidden.title: aria-hidden

aria-invalid.description: Indicates the entered value does not conform to the format expected by the application.
aria-invalid.title: aria-invalid

aria-keyshortcuts.description: Indicates keyboard shortcuts that an author has implemented to activate or give focus to an element.
aria-keyshortcuts.title: aria-keyshortcuts

aria-label.description: Defines a string value that labels the current element.
aria-label.title: aria-label

aria-labelledby.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that labels the current element.
aria-labelledby.title: aria-labelledby

aria-level.description: Defines the hierarchical level of an element within a structure.
aria-level.title: aria-level

aria-live.description: Indicates that an element will be updated, and describes the types of updates the user agents, assistive technologies, and user can expect from the live region.
aria-live.title: aria-live

aria-modal.description: Indicates whether an element is modal when displayed.
aria-modal.title: aria-modal

aria-multiline.description: Indicates whether a text box accepts multiple lines of input or only a single line.
aria-multiline.title: aria-multiline

aria-multiselectable.description: Indicates that the user may select more than one item from the current selectable descendants.
aria-multiselectable.title: aria-multiselectable

aria-orientation.description: Indicates whether the element's orientation is horizontal, vertical, or unknown/ambiguous.
aria-orientation.title: aria-orientation

aria-owns.description:
Identifies an element (or elements) in order to define a visual, functional, or contextual parent/child relationship
between DOM elements where the DOM hierarchy cannot be used to represent the relationship.
aria-owns.title: aria-owns

aria-placeholder.description:
Defines a short hint (a word or short phrase) intended to aid the user with data entry when the control has no value.
A hint could be a sample value or a brief description of the expected format.
aria-placeholder.title: aria-placeholder

aria-posinset.description: Defines an element's number or position in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.
aria-posinset.title: aria-posinset

aria-pressed.description: Indicates the current "pressed" state of toggle buttons.
aria-pressed.title: aria-pressed

aria-readonly.description: Indicates that the element is not editable, but is otherwise operable.
aria-readonly.title: aria-readonly

aria-relevant.description: Indicates what notifications the user agent will trigger when the accessibility tree within a live region is modified.
aria-relevant.title: aria-relevant

aria-required.description: Indicates that user input is required on the element before a form may be submitted.
aria-required.title: aria-required

aria-roledescription.description: Defines a human-readable, author-localized description for the role of an element.
aria-roledescription.title: aria-roledescription

aria-rowcount.description: Defines the total number of rows in a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-rowcount.title: aria-rowcount

aria-rowindex.description: Defines an element's row index or position with respect to the total number of rows within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-rowindex.title: aria-rowindex

aria-rowindextext.description: Defines a human readable text alternative of aria-rowindex.
aria-rowindextext.title: aria-rowindextext

aria-rowspan.description: Defines the number of rows spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-rowspan.title: aria-rowspan

aria-selected.description: Indicates the current "selected" state of various widgets.
aria-selected.title: aria-selected

aria-setsize.description: Defines the number of items in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.
aria-setsize.title: aria-setsize

aria-sort.description: Indicates if items in a table or grid are sorted in ascending or descending order.
aria-sort.title: aria-sort

aria-valuemax.description: Defines the maximum allowed value for a range widget.
aria-valuemax.title: aria-valuemax

aria-valuemin.description: Defines the minimum allowed value for a range widget.
aria-valuemin.title: aria-valuemin

aria-valuenow.description: Defines the current value for a range widget.
aria-valuenow.title: aria-valuenow

aria-valuetext.description: Defines the human readable text alternative of aria-valuenow for a range widget.
aria-valuetext.title: aria-valuetext

display.description:
The display property sets whether an box is treated as a block or inline element and the layout used for its children,
such as grid or flex.
display.title: display

justifyContent.description:
The justifyContent property defines how the browser distributes space between and around content items along
the main-axis of a flex container, and the inline axis of a grid container.
justifyContent.title: justifyContent

maxWidth.description: The max width property specifies the width of a box's content area.
maxWidth.title: maxWidth

maxHeight.description: The max height property specifies the height of a box's content area.
maxHeight.title: maxHeight

minWidth.description: The min width property specifies the width of a box's content area.
minWidth.title: minWidth

minHeight.description: The min height property specifies the height of a box's content area.
minHeight.title: minHeight

flex.description: This is the shorthand for flexGrow, flexShrink and flexBasis combined.
flex.title: flex

flexGrow.description: This defines the ability for a flex item to grow if necessary.
flexGrow.title: flexGrow

flexWrap.description: The flexWrap property sets whether flex items are forced onto one line or can wrap onto multiple lines.
flexWrap.title: flexWrap

order.description: The order property controls the order in which they appear in a flex container.
order.title: order

gridTemplateColumns.description: The gridTemplateColumns property defines the line names and track sizing functions of the grid columns.
gridTemplateColumns.title: gridTemplateColumns

gridTemplateAreas.description: The gridTemplateAreas property specifies named grid areas, establishing the cells in the grid and assigning them names.
gridTemplateAreas.title: gridTemplateAreas

gridTemplateRows.description: The gridTemplateRows property defines the line names and track sizing functions of the grid rows.
gridTemplateRows.title: gridTemplateRows

gridArea.description:
The gridArea shorthand property specifies a grid item's size and location within a grid by contributing a line,
a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the edges of its grid area.
gridArea.title: gridArea

flexDirection.description: The flexDirection property sets how flex items are placed in the flex container defining the main axis and the direction.
flexDirection.title: flexDirection

alignItems.description:
The alignItems property sets the align-self value on all direct children as a group. In Flexbox, it controls the alignment of items on the Cross Axis.
In Grid Layout, it controls the alignment of items on the Block Axis within their grid area.
alignItems.title: alignItems

alignSelf.description:
The alignSelf property overrides a grid or flex item's align-items value. In Grid, it aligns the item inside the grid area.
In Flexbox, it aligns the item on the cross axis.
alignSelf.title: alignSelf

gap.description: The gap property sets the gaps between rows and columns. It is a shorthand for rowGap and columnGap.
gap.title: gap

gridGap.description: The gridGap property sets the gaps between rows and columns. It is a shorthand for rowGap and columnGap.
gridGap.title: gridGap

pointerEvents.description: The pointerEvents property sets under what circumstances (if any) a particular graphic element can become the target of pointer events.
pointerEvents.title: pointerEvents

overflow.description: The overflow shorthand property sets the desired behavior for an box's overflow.
overflow.title: overflow

overflowX.description: The overflow-x property sets what shows when content overflows a block-level box's left and right edges.
overflowX.title: overflowX

overflowY.description: The overflow-y property sets what shows when content overflows a block-level box's top and bottom edges.
overflowY.title: overflowY

cursor.description: The cursor property sets the mouse cursor, if any, to show when the mouse pointer is over an box.
cursor.title: cursor

backgroundColor.description: The backgroundColor property sets the background color of the box.
backgroundColor.title: backgroundColor

borderRadius.description: The borderRadius property rounds the corners of an box's outer border edge.
borderRadius.title: borderRadius

borderTopWidth.description: The borderTopWidth property defines the width of the border at the top of a box.
borderTopWidth.title: borderTopWidth

borderBottomWidth.description: The borderBottomWidth property defines the width of the border at the bottom of a box.
borderBottomWidth.title: borderBottomWidth

borderLeftWidth.description: The borderLeftWidth property defines the width of the border at the left of a box.
borderLeftWidth.title: borderLeftWidth

borderWidthX.description: The borderWidthX shorthand property defines the width of the element's border on the left and right.
borderWidthX.title: borderWidthX

borderWidthY.description: The borderWidthY shorthand property defines the width of the element's border on the top and bottom.
borderWidthY.title: borderWidthY

boxSizing.description: The boxSizing property sets how the total width and height of an box is calculated.
boxSizing.title: boxSizing

boxShadow.description: The boxShadow property adds shadow effects around an box's frame.
boxShadow.title: boxShadow

padding.description: The padding properties are used to generate space around an box's content area.
padding.title: padding

paddingTop.description: The paddingTop property sets the height of the padding area on the top of an box.
paddingTop.title: paddingTop

paddingBottom.description: The paddingBottom property sets the height of the padding area on the bottom of an box.
paddingBottom.title: paddingBottom

paddingLeft.description: The paddingLeft property sets the width of the padding area to the left of an box.
paddingLeft.title: paddingLeft

paddingRight.description: The paddingLeft property sets the width of the padding area to the right of an box.
paddingRight.title: paddingRight

margin.description: The margin shorthand property sets the margin area on all four sides of an box.
margin.title: margin

marginTop.description: The marginTop property sets the margin area on the top of an box.
marginTop.title: marginTop

marginBottom.description: The marginBottom property sets the margin area on the bottom of an box.
marginBottom.title: marginBottom

marginLeft.description: The marginLeft property sets the margin area on the left side of an box.
marginLeft.title: marginLeft

marginRight.description: The marginRight property sets the margin area on the right side of an box.
marginRight.title: marginRight

transitionDelay.description: The transitionDelay property specifies the duration to wait before starting a property's transition effect when its value changes.
transitionDelay.title: transitionDelay

zIndex.description: The zIndex property specifies the stack order of the box.
zIndex.title: zIndex

background.description: The background property sets the background of the box.
background.title: background

backgroundImage.description: The backgroundImage property sets one or more background images on an element.
backgroundImage.title: backgroundImage

backgroundPosition.description:
The backgroundPosition property sets the initial position for each background image.
The position is relative to the position layer set by background-origin.
backgroundPosition.title: backgroundPosition

backgroundBlendMode.description:
The backgroundBlendMode property sets how an element's background images should blend with each

**Initial value**: `stretch`

boxOrdinalGroup.description:

The **`box-direction`** CSS property specifies whether a box lays out its contents normally (from the top or left edge), or in reverse (from the bottom or right edge).

**Syntax**: `normal | reverse | inherit`

**Initial value**: `normal`
WebkitBoxDirection.title: WebkitBoxDirection

WebkitBoxFlex.description:
The **`-moz-box-flex`** and **`-webkit-box-flex`** CSS properties specify how a `-moz-box` or `-webkit-box` grows to fill the box that contains it, in the direction of the containing box's layout.

**Syntax**: `<number>`

**Initial value**: `0`
WebkitBoxFlex.title: WebkitBoxFlex

WebkitBoxFlexGroup.description:
The **`box-flex-group`** CSS property assigns the flexbox's child elements to a flex group.

**Syntax**: `<integer>`

**Initial value**: `1`
WebkitBoxFlexGroup.title: WebkitBoxFlexGroup

WebkitBoxLines.description:
The **`box-lines`** CSS property determines whether the box may have a single or multiple lines (rows for horizontally oriented boxes, columns for vertically oriented boxes).

**Syntax**: `single | multiple`

**Initial value**: `single`
WebkitBoxLines.title: WebkitBoxLines

WebkitBoxOrdinalGroup.description:
The **`box-ordinal-group`** CSS property assigns the flexbox's child elements to an ordinal group.

**Syntax**: `<integer>`

**Initial value**: `1`
WebkitBoxOrdinalGroup.title: WebkitBoxOrdinalGroup

WebkitBoxOrient.description:
The **`box-orient`** CSS property sets whether an element lays out its contents horizontally or vertically.

**Syntax**: `horizontal | vertical | inline-axis | block-axis | inherit`

**Initial value**: `inline-axis`
WebkitBoxOrient.title: WebkitBoxOrient

WebkitBoxPack.description:
The **`-moz-box-pack`** and **`-webkit-box-pack`** CSS properties specify how a `-moz-box` or `-webkit-box` packs its contents in the direction of its layout. The effect of this is only visible if there is extra space in the box.

**Syntax**: `start | center | end | justify`

**Initial value**: `start`
WebkitBoxPack.title: WebkitBoxPack

inputMode.description: Hints at the type of data that might be entered by the user while editing the element or its contents
inputMode.title: inputMode

is.description: Specify that a standard HTML element should behave like a defined custom built-in element
is.title: is

aria-activedescendant.description: Identifies the currently active element when DOM focus is on a composite widget, textbox, group, or application.
aria-activedescendant.title: aria-activedescendant

aria-atomic.description: Indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the aria-relevant attribute.
aria-atomic.title: aria-atomic

aria-autocomplete.description:
Indicates whether inputting text could trigger display of one or more predictions of the user's intended value for an input and specifies how predictions would be
presented if they are made.
aria-autocomplete.title: aria-autocomplete

aria-braillelabel.description: Defines a string value that labels the current element, which is intended to be converted into Braille.
aria-braillelabel.title: aria-braillelabel

aria-brailleroledescription.description: Defines a human-readable, author-localized abbreviated description for the role of an element, which is intended to be converted into Braille.
aria-brailleroledescription.title: aria-brailleroledescription

aria-checked.description: Indicates the current "checked" state of checkboxes, radio buttons, and other widgets.
aria-checked.title: aria-checked

aria-colcount.description: Defines the total number of columns in a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-colcount.title: aria-colcount

aria-colindex.description: Defines an element's column index or position with respect to the total number of columns within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-colindex.title: aria-colindex

aria-colindextext.description: Defines a human readable text alternative of aria-colindex.
aria-colindextext.title: aria-colindextext

aria-colspan.description: Defines the number of columns spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-colspan.title: aria-colspan

aria-controls.description: Identifies the element (or elements) whose contents or presence are controlled by the current element.
aria-controls.title: aria-controls

aria-current.description: Indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.
aria-current.title: aria-current

aria-describedby.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that describes the object.
aria-describedby.title: aria-describedby

aria-description.description: Defines a string value that describes or annotates the current element.
aria-description.title: aria-description

aria-details.description: Identifies the element that provides a detailed, extended description for the object.
aria-details.title: aria-details

aria-disabled.description: Indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable.
aria-disabled.title: aria-disabled

aria-dropeffect.description: Indicates what functions can be performed when a dragged object is released on the drop target.
aria-dropeffect.title: aria-dropeffect

aria-errormessage.description: Identifies the element that provides an error message for the object.
aria-errormessage.title: aria-errormessage

aria-expanded.description: Indicates whether the element, or another grouping element it controls, is currently expanded or collapsed.
aria-expanded.title: aria-expanded

aria-flowto.description:
Identifies the next element (or elements) in an alternate reading order of content which, at the user's discretion,
allows assistive technology to override the general default of reading in document source order.
aria-flowto.title: aria-flowto

aria-grabbed.description: Indicates an element's "grabbed" state in a drag-and-drop operation.
aria-grabbed.title: aria-grabbed

aria-haspopup.description: Indicates the availability and type of interactive popup element, such as menu or dialog, that can be triggered by an element.
aria-haspopup.title: aria-haspopup

aria-hidden.description: Indicates whether the element is exposed to an accessibility API.
aria-hidden.title: aria-hidden

aria-invalid.description: Indicates the entered value does not conform to the format expected by the application.
aria-invalid.title: aria-invalid

aria-keyshortcuts.description: Indicates keyboard shortcuts that an author has implemented to activate or give focus to an element.
aria-keyshortcuts.title: aria-keyshortcuts

aria-label.description: Defines a string value that labels the current element.
aria-label.title: aria-label

aria-labelledby.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that labels the current element.
aria-labelledby.title: aria-labelledby

aria-level.description: Defines the hierarchical level of an element within a structure.
aria-level.title: aria-level

aria-live.description: Indicates that an element will be updated, and describes the types of updates the user agents, assistive technologies, and user can expect from the live region.
aria-live.title: aria-live

aria-modal.description: Indicates whether an element is modal when displayed.
aria-modal.title: aria-modal

aria-multiline.description: Indicates whether a text box accepts multiple lines of input or only a single line.
aria-multiline.title: aria-multiline

aria-multiselectable.description: Indicates that the user may select more than one item from the current selectable descendants.
aria-multiselectable.title: aria-multiselectable

aria-orientation.description: Indicates whether the element's orientation is horizontal, vertical, or unknown/ambiguous.
aria-orientation.title: aria-orientation

aria-owns.description:
Identifies an element (or elements) in order to define a visual, functional, or contextual parent/child relationship
between DOM elements where the DOM hierarchy cannot be used to represent the relationship.
aria-owns.title: aria-owns

aria-placeholder.description:
Defines a short hint (a word or short phrase) intended to aid the user with data entry when the control has no value.
A hint could be a sample value or a brief description of the expected format.
aria-placeholder.title: aria-placeholder

aria-posinset.description: Defines an element's number or position in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.
aria-posinset.title: aria-posinset

aria-pressed.description: Indicates the current "pressed" state of toggle buttons.
aria-pressed.title: aria-pressed

aria-readonly.description: Indicates that the element is not editable, but is otherwise operable.
aria-readonly.title: aria-readonly

aria-relevant.description: Indicates what notifications the user agent will trigger when the accessibility tree within a live region is modified.
aria-relevant.title: aria-relevant

aria-required.description: Indicates that user input is required on the element before a form may be submitted.
aria-required.title: aria-required

aria-roledescription.description: Defines a human-readable, author-localized description for the role of an element.
aria-roledescription.title: aria-roledescription

aria-rowcount.description: Defines the total number of rows in a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-rowcount.title: aria-rowcount

aria-rowindex.description: Defines an element's row index or position with respect to the total number of rows within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-rowindex.title: aria-rowindex

aria-rowindextext.description: Defines a human readable text alternative of aria-rowindex.
aria-rowindextext.title: aria-rowindextext

aria-rowspan.description: Defines the number of rows spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
aria-rowspan.title: aria-rowspan

aria-selected.description: Indicates the current "selected" state of various widgets.
aria-selected.title: aria-selected

aria-setsize.description: Defines the number of items in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.
aria-setsize.title: aria-setsize

aria-sort.description: Indicates if items in a table or grid are sorted in ascending or descending order.
aria-sort.title: aria-sort

aria-valuemax.description: Defines the maximum allowed value for a range widget.
aria-valuemax.title: aria-valuemax

aria-valuemin.description: Defines the minimum allowed value for a range widget.
aria-valuemin.title: aria-valuemin

aria-valuenow.description: Defines the current value for a range widget.
aria-valuenow.title: aria-valuenow

aria-valuetext.description: Defines the human readable text alternative of aria-valuenow for a range widget.
aria-valuetext.title: aria-valuetext
